es.  P20 is produced in the P20 Plant (at the Trona Facility) and it can be described as a 50% weight solution of specific phenolic compounds in a kerosene base.  The purpose of P20 is to provide the raw material for making the extractant utilized at the LLX plant.



The P20 Plant boundaries encompass approximately 5000 square feet of the LLX plant.  P20 is manufactured in a batch process (currently one batch per day on average) in which each batch consists of approximately 900 gallons of P20 product.  P20 product is stored in a tank for use at the LLX Plant to produce extractant.



Chlorine and 37-percent concentrated formaldehyde solution (both of which are regulated substances) alongwith other raw materials are used in the manufacture of P20 Product.  Chlorine, in one ton containers, is used in a batch process in which a measured amount of liquid chlorine is fed from a one-ton container, through a chlorine vaporizer, to an intermediate process reactor in which para-nonylphenol is chlorinated.  This intermediate product (chlorinated para-nonylphenol) is then used as one of the raw materials alongwith 37-percent concentrated formaldehyde solution in the presence of sodium hydroxide, water and borax at controlled temperatures and retention times for the manufacture of the P20 Product.  



The storage, handling and use system for chlorine at the Trona Facility consists of the following:

?    Receipt of one-ton chlorine containers;

?    Unloading/Loading hoist;

?    Five one-ton containers in a storage area;

?    A one-ton container weighing station;

?    Liquid chlorine transfer pipelines;

?    A liquid chlorine evaporator area;

?    Gas chlorine transfer pipelines;

?    A fumes scrubber system;

?    Chlorine absorber system; 

?    Cooling water pipeline; and

?    Process instrumentation and detection and monitoring devices;



The formaldehyde storage, handling and use system at the Trona Facility consists of the following:

?    A condensation reaction area;

?    Transition product pipeli

nes and product pipeline;

?    Formaldehyde storage tank and containment area;

?    Formaldehyde transfer lines and transfer pump; 

?    Sodium Hydroxide, borax, water and kerosene transfer lines; 

